Keep in mind the &quot;prompt&quot; is a browser feature. The browser you are using may not support asking a user for credentials.

If you want to be assured you get a prompt, the best way is actually to use FORM authentication and create a custom HTML form.

EDIT
==== 

Examine what is being sent back to the browser. If there isn&#39;t a `WWW-Authenticate: Basic` header, the browser won&#39;t know what to do. I have a feeling this is because you are missing the Realm element in your login config:

```
&lt;login-config&gt;
  &lt;auth-method&gt;BASIC&lt;/auth-method&gt;
  &lt;realm-name&gt;MySecurityRealm&lt;/realm-name&gt;
&lt;/login-config&gt;
```

